<H3> <TI>   Businessmen Request Plebiscite </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Businessmen Request Plebiscite </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0705030794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0705030794 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Seven O'Clock News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Colombia's industrialists and businessmen have said 
a referendum is needed to determine whether minimum doses of 
drugs for personal consumption should be legalized. Alberto 
Vasquez Restrepo, president of Colombian Chamber of 
Construction, spoke on behalf of 14 economic associations. 
  [Begin Vasquez recording] As we said in a communique sent to 
the president today, we are absolutely dumbfounded. This 
decision has really taken the country by surprise and we have 
asked the president to invoke the constitutional right to 
consult the people on any subject. This right to a referendum 
is needed more than ever today, considering that there is no 
higher body above the Constitutional Court to which this 
decision can be appealed in order to abolish or modify it. [end 
recording]. 

</TEXT>

