<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Opposed to All Unilateral Actions in Haiti' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government `Opposed to All Unilateral Actions in Haiti' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0605151294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1428 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0605151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Montevideo, 6 May (EFE) -- Foreign Minister Sergio 
Abreu announced today that Uruguay is opposed to all unilateral 
actions in Haiti and will promote a rapid OAS intervention to 
prevent a deterioration of the situation in the Caribbean island. 
  "Uruguay is a staunch defender of the principle of 
non-intervention and the self-determination of nations," said 
Abreu during a news conference with international correspondents 
in Montevideo. 
  He stressed his country's concern over an eventual 
unilateral 
U.S. intervention to resolve the crisis in Haiti. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

