<H3> <TI>   TE Preliminary Results: PRD Leading </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TE Preliminary Results: PRD Leading </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0905015994 Panama City Television Network in Spanish 0115 
GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0905015994 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Report" by Panamanian Electoral Tribunal President Eduardo </F>
Valdes Escoffery from the Atlapa Convention Center in Panama 
City -- live] 
  [Text] In the number of voting sites accounted for, an 
abstention rate of 27.48 percent has been reported. Therefore, 
72.52 percent of the registered voters participated in the 
elections. This is the breakdown of 11.8 percent of voting 
sites tallied. You will be given more details, for consultation 
purposes, as soon as we finish giving this report. 
  Candidate Ernesto Perez Balladares of the United People 
Alliance received 32.8 percent of the valid votes. Next comes 
Mireya Moscoso de Gruber of Democratic Alliance with 30.12 
percent. Ruben Carles of the Change '94 Alliance comes in third 
with 16.92 percent. Ruben Blades of the Papa Egoro Movement 
placed fourth with 15.89 percent. Edy Vallarino of the Christian 
Democratic Party comes in fifth with 2.54 percent. Sammy Lewis 
Galindo of Concertacion Nacional attained 1.44 percent and 
occupies sixth place. Jose Salvador Munoz of the Doctrinaire 
Panamenista Party brings up the rear with 0.21 percent. 
  These figures will be made available in a few minutes 
through 
the television system we have set up for you. This information 
will be updated approximately every 10 minutes from now on via 
the systems you people have been trained to consult. Thank you. 

</TEXT>

