<H3> <TI>   Civil Aeronautics Institute Note on Hijacking </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civil Aeronautics Institute Note on Hijacking </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0905075894 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 0709 GMT 9 May 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA0905075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 9 May (PL) -- Today, the Cuban Civil 
Aeronautics Institute described as an "act of air piracy" the 
hijacking to Miami of a Cubana de Aviacion flight (CUB-9100) 
with several passengers on board. 
  In a press note released in this capital, the institute said 
the passengers of the hijacked plane, which was covering the 
Havana-Nassau route, were transported to their destination from 
that U.S. city. 
  The official note said the AN-24 airplane returned to Havana 
with the rest of the crew, and confirmed that the plane was 
hijacked yesterday by pilot Basilio Garcia Breto. 

</TEXT>

