<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 9 May, it was made known that Fidel Castro wrote 
a message to Mandela. The text of the message highlights the 
happiness of the Cuban people with the creation of a democratic, 
multiracial government headed by an antiapartheid leader. Castro 
expressed Cuba's willingness to establish diplomatic relations, 
as well as to assist and support the Government of South Africa 
during this new phase. 

</TEXT>

