<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nigerian Ambassador on Conflict With Cameroon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nigerian Ambassador on Conflict With Cameroon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0605231794 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0605231794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nigerian Ambassador to Havana Y. Alhassan stated 
today in Havana during a news conference that his government 
will maintain its peaceful policy, but will be firm against any 
attack from the Republic of Cameroon. 
  The Nigerian ambassador provided broad information on the 
border conflict between the two countries in the Bakassi 
peninsula zone which has always belonged to Nigeria, as 
confirmed by several treaties, although Cameroon is now 
expressing some designs on this territory. 
  The ambassador added that the strengthening of Nigerian 
forces, to maintain order in that region, has been 
misinterpreted by the neighboring country, which conducted three 
military attacks in February 1994. He added that Nigeria will 
never be the first to attack, but that its armed forces are 
prepared for anything. 

</TEXT>

