<H3> <TI>   PANPRA Urges Concessions From Aristide, Cedras </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PANPRA Urges Concessions From Aristide, Cedras </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0905210794 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1600 
GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0905210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PANPRA [Nationalistic Progressive Revolutionary 
Party of Haiti] leader Serge Gilles calls on the political 
parties to meet immediately to analyze the latest situation. 
  [Begin Gilles recording in Creole] I would like to send this 
call to all political leaders, especially the moderate ones; all 
Haitian political leaders; all Haitian political parties that 
belong to the center. This does not mean that I exclude the 
others, but I think the moderates can understand me better. They 
must meet, they must discuss, they must issue a statement in 
which they clearly express their position to the international 
community. I am also calling on the social sectors, all the 
labor unions, to put their heads together to find a consensus, 
to express their position, and to make the international 
community know that if the new sanctions are applied, the 
Haitian people will disappear. 
  Finally, my call goes out to General Cedras and President 
Aristide to do their best, to make all possible and imaginary 
concessions in order to solve the problem within the framework 
of the parliamentary plan. I believe it is possible. [end 
