<H3> <TI>   Island To Remain Under Netherlands' Supervision </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Island To Remain Under Netherlands' Supervision </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0905125194 Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT in Dutch 7 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BR0905125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Cabinet Lengthens Supervision of St. </F>
Maarten"] 
  [Text] The Hague -- The island of St. Maarten is to remain 
under supervision. At Minister Hirsch Ballin's proposal, the 
cabinet agreed to lengthen the current supervision arrangement 
to 1 September of this year. 
  The decision gives the new Pourier government of the 
Netherlands Antilles, sworn in on 31 March, the time to set up a 
new administrative structure for the island. 
  The reason the government was put under supervision was the 
financial and administrative mismanagement suffered over the 
past few years under the leadership of local leader C. Wathey. 
Wathey is the suspect in a criminal investigation into fraud 
worth millions surrounding the enlargement of the airport and 
harbor on the island. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

