<H3> <TI>   Attorney General's Office Denies Links to Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attorney General's Office Denies Links to Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0705023494 Mexico City UNOMASUNO in Spanish 4 May 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> PA0705023494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City UNOMASUNO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Attorney General's office (PGR) has denied it 
wrote a confidential report that was published yesterday by EL 
FINANCIERO. The document makes various comments on the last six 
presidential terms and issues some statements, which the PGR 
called undignified and groundless. A PGR communique said the 
contents of the confidential report, which was signed by two of 
the newspaper's reporters, was not prepared by any of its 
agencies because its functions "have nothing to do with the 
analyses the reporters make in the document." In turn, the PGR 
claims it is not responsible for the document. 

</TEXT>

