<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministers View Meeting With Taiwanese Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministers View Meeting With Taiwanese Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0605172694 Managua EL NUEVO DIARIO in Spanish 5 May 94 pp 
1, 8 </F>

<F P=103> PA0605172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua EL NUEVO DIARIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Irma Franco] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Cooperation Minister Erwin Kruger reported 
that during the first working meeting between the Taiwanese 
president's delegation and the Chamorro cabinet officials from 
both nations acknowledged the economic progress made in four 
years of government with the support of the Republic of China 
and the pardoning of 75 percent of Nicaragua's debt. 
  This working meeting was attended by the minister-president 
of the Council of Economic Planning and Development, the 
president of the Federation of Industries and Chambers of 
Commerce, and the minister-president of the Central Bank of 
Taiwan. 
  Social Action Minister William Baez, the Central Bank 
president, the foreign relations minister, and the economy 
minister represented Nicaragua. 
  Among the topics discussed were the structural adjustment, 
economic stabilization, foreign cooperation, continued support, 
and the market economy. 
  Kruger affirmed that a document pardoning 75 percent of 
Nicaragua's debt with Taiwan and outlining cooperation for the 
1994-96 period will be signed today. The cooperation accord 
will be defined in this second round of meetings. 
  Social Action Minister William Baez said the meeting was 
fruitful because the economic cabinet was able to explain the 
problems with the debt payment. He added that the Taiwanese 
officials expressed their firm interest in continuing to support 
Nicaragua. 
  Baez asserted that the issue that most impressed the 
Taiwanese delegation was the 20-percent growth in the 
agricultural sector, a figure they considered very high. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

