<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRD Accused of Buying Votes, Stealing Ballots </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRD Accused of Buying Votes, Stealing Ballots </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0905172594 Panama City EL SIGLO in Spanish 9 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PA0905172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL SIGLO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Leaks and Tips" column] </F>
  [Text] In violation of electoral provisions, some PRD 
[Democratic Revolutionary Party] candidates in various electoral 
districts offered to buy votes with payments ranging from 
$20-$30 per vote. This was also an old practice of ousted 
General Manuel Antonio Noriega's associates. The Office of the 
Electoral Prosecutor should immediately conduct a detailed 
investigation of this crime. The purchase of votes occurred in 
Cabuya, Anton... Parque Lefevre... Rio Abajo, as well as in 
David and Puerto Armuelles. [ellipses as published] 
  At the Salinera voting table in Nata, even presidential 
ballots were stolen. These ballots, according to what was 
learned, were removed by PRD activists. Also, in Chitre, Ocu, 
and Parita, PRD activists protested at several voting stations 
with other parties. The PRD activists arrived at the time of 
closing of the voting tables to cast their votes, which is 
illegal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

