<H3> <TI>   Dario Carles Unwilling To Participate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dario Carles Unwilling To Participate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0905200294 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0905200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Telemetro Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with presidential candidate Ruben Dario Carles of </F>
the Change `94 coalition by an unidentified reporter; place not 
given; from the "Telemetro Reports" newscast -- live] 
  [Text] [Reporter] Professor Carles, would you be willing to 
participate in the PRD [Democratic Revolutionary Party] 
government, should you be invited to do so? 
  [Carles] I have no personal interest in participating in any 
government. As president, I would have had the opportunity and 
the authority to do the things that we had proposed, and that we 
had planned, [words indistinct] I do not believe I could 
transfer those goals, that vision, and that determination to any 
group. Political problems will have to be resolved in another 
manner, not through my individual participation. That is 
another issue altogether. We are going to have to unite as 
Panamanians to safeguard justice, liberty, and democracy in this 
country. 
  I invite Ruben Blades to stay here in Panama to fight for 
Panamanians. This is why Blades said as a candidate that: This 
is the time to face problems and to struggle for justice, 
freedom, and democracy... [pauses] and for all those other 
things that were not very clear in his speeches. 

</TEXT>

