<H3> <TI>   President Congratulates Leaders on PLO Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Congratulates Leaders on PLO Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0905121394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2228 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY0905121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 6 May (EFE) -- Today, Brazilian President 
Itamar Franco sent congratulatory messages to Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat following 
the recent agreement to establish a Palestine Self-Government 
Authority [Autoridad Palestina de Auto-Gobierno]. 
  The decision to create a provisional Palestine 
Self-Government Authority with jurisdiction on the Palestine 
territories in the Gaza Strip and Jericho is considered 
"historic" by the Brazilian chief of state. 
  Franco points out that the agreement represents a new 
horizon 
for the consolidation of peace, safety, and stability in the 
Middle East that will benefit the region and all of humanity. 
  Egyptian President Husni Mubarak, who hosted the 
Rabin-Arafat 
meeting held in Cairo on 4 May, also received a congratulatory 
message from Franco. 

</TEXT>

