<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pastrana Supports Response to U.S. on de Greiff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pastrana Supports Response to U.S. on de Greiff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0805012294 Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO in Spanish 4 May 
94 p 11A </F>

<F P=103> PA0805012294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL TIEMPO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The Colombia Government has replied to the U.S. 
State Department letter in accordance to its duty: to defend the 
honesty of the institutions and judicial authorities." 
Presidential candidate Andres Pastrana has made this statement 
as he expressed his support for the Colombian response to the 18 
April U.S. letter questioning Prosecutor General Gustavo de 
Greiff's attitude. 
  Pastrana said: "It is worrisome that as policies of 
submission are enforced, certain self-confessed criminals 
tarnish the names of other parties and even the image of an 
entire country so as to have their sentences reduced for 
allegedly collaborating with authorities." 
  Pastrana also urged the two governments to reestablish the 
lines of communication, to normalize bilateral relations, and to 
reactivate the mechanisms of judicial collaboration to fight 
international drug trafficking. 
  Meanwhile, Pastrana reiterated his opposition to the 
legalization of drugs, saying: "Should Senator Kerry or any 
other U.S. authority have substantial information that will 
contribute to preventing drug trafficking from interfering with 
Colombian politics, he must say so immediately by providing the 
details he knows." 

</TEXT>

