<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Proposal Made To Hold Plebiscite Along With Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Proposal Made To Hold Plebiscite Along With Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0605155594 Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 
29 Apr 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PY0605155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With the approval of two-fifths of Congress, 52 
legislators from the National [Blanco] Party, the Radical 
Battleist Ticket No. 15 [Battlismo Radical Lista 15], and the 
Colorado and Battleist Union (UCB) will promote in early May a 
constitutional reform project that will be subjected to a 
plebiscite along with the national elections scheduled for 
November. 
  Congressional sources told EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO that this 
proposal also is allegedly approved by legislators of the Party 
of the Government by the People, who disapprove of the agreement 
with the Battleist Forum. 
  The main proposal reportedly approves multiparty votes [voto 
cruzado], involving the election of a presidential candidate 
from a party and a mayor from another party. 

</TEXT>

