Clasico Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The National Newscast"] </F>
  A partial transportation sector strike in Caracas was 
resolved this afternoon. [Words indistinct] once a meeting with 
the top transportation and communications authorities. In the 
country there is a climate of social unrest and dissatisfaction 
resulting from the economic crisis, said Government Minister 
Ramon Escovar Salom at the presidential building. He said that, 
despite the partial transportation sector strike, there is calm 
in the country. 
  [Begin Escovar recording] The people are fed up with the 
interruption of normal life in Venezuelan cities. The people 
want peace, calm, and work. They want to be able to work in 
peace. Hence, all movements aimed at stopping normal activities 
in the country are doomed to fail sooner or later. The people 
repudiate these alterations of public order. And this will be 
clearly demonstrated in a few days. The government enjoys the 
nation's trust because strikes will not resolve the current 
difficulties. These interruptions only aggravate the economic 
crisis and prevent the country from concentrating its resources 
to overcome the crisis. Those who can aggravate the crisis can 
declare strikes but they are resisted by the country's majority. 
This is what I have to say today. The reports I have received 
is that the country is calm. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

