<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Attorney General, Prosecutor General Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Attorney General, Prosecutor General Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0805162494 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1923 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0805162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 7 May (ACAN-EFE) -- Guatemalan 
President Ramiro de Leon Carpio today appointed lawyers Acisclo 
Valladares as the new attorney general and Ranses Cuestas as the 
new prosecutor general. Valladares is reassuming the post he 
held during the government of overthrown President Jorge Serrano 
(1991-1993). 
  Before swearing in the new officials, President de Leon 
Carpio explained that the new attorney general will serve as an 
adviser and consultant to state institutions. 
  Valladares left office in 1993 after being suspended. At 
that time the courts charged that Valladares had refrained from 
bringing fraud charges against his brother Luis Domingo 
Valladares. 
  Presidency sources told ACAN-EFE that Cuestas, a lawyer with 
30 years experience, has never held a public office. 
  Valladares and Cuestas will assume the offices Telesforo 
Guerra Cahn held simultaneously. The attorney general was 
chosen directly by the president while the prosecutor general 
was chosen from among six candidates presented by a nominating 
committee headed by the Supreme Court of Justice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

