<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Reports Resignation of Army Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Reports Resignation of Army Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0705195594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0154 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0705195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 5 May (EFE) -- Today, Ecuadoran Defense 
Minister General Jose Gallardo announced the resignation of 
Ecuadoran Army Commander General Edmundo Luna, who will be 
replaced by Gen. Victor Bayas, current Army chief of staff. 
Gallardo explained the change is part of a process of normal 
renewal in the Armed Forcues and denied that there is a dispute 
within that institution. 
  "Gen. Edmundo Luna has asked for a discharge and will be 
replaced in the next few days through the normal Armed Forces 
promotion process," Gallardo added. The defense minister 
concluded that Gen. Alfonso Alarcon, chief of the Armed Forces 
Joint Command, will also be replaced in the next few days. His 
successor will be appointed by President Sixto Duran-Ballen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

