<H3> <TI>   Matanzas Power Plant Resumes Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Matanzas Power Plant Resumes Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL1005144994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1005144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Matanzas correspondent Manolo Garcia] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Antonio Guiteras 
thermoelectric plant in Matanzas is operating at full capacity 
and absolute efficiency. This plant resumed operations Saturday 
afternoon after a brief 72-hour down time period for maintenance. 
  Engineer Jesus Valdez Torra, plant director, reported that 
all defects have been fully eradicated. Therefore, the plant 
will be fully operative until the next maintenance period, which 
will require six days. 
  The engineer added that maintenance work will also be done 
on 
another 330 megawatt unit. This work will include regulating the 
valves and cleaning the boiler walls. 
  The Antonio Guiteras plant has provided more than 500,000 
megawatt-hours to date and expects to conclude the year with a 
total of 2.2 million megawatt-hours, 10 percent of the total 
amount of electricity generated by Cuba's Electric Union. 

</TEXT>

