<H3> <TI>   Senators Plan To Appoint `Temporary' President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senators Plan To Appoint `Temporary' President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105011394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2315 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1105011394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Port-au-Prince, 10 May (EFE) -- A group of senators, 
who were elected on 18 January 1993 in elections described as 
fraudulent, are planning to appoint Judge Emile Jonassain, 
former Supreme Court president, as temporary Haitian president 
tomorrow, 11 May. 
  The legislators, led by Bernard Sansaricq, who leads one of 
the Senate Board of Directors, made the decision today during a 
session described as irregular. Nevertheless, Jonassain said he 
is officially unaware of the decision. 
  Sansaricq sent Jonassain a copy of the decree adopted during 
the session, which has been described as illegal. He also sent 
a copy to General Raoul Cedras, Armed Forces chief, and Frantz 
Robert Monde, president of the Chamber of Deputies. 

</TEXT>

