<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Economic Developments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1005204294 </F>
<F P=103> PA1005204294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports economic developments monitored through 10 May. 
  Agriculture Minister Juan Rafael Lizano reported on 4 May 
that agricultural exports represented 67 percent of the total 
exports in 1993 and have increased 4.5 percent over the past 
four years. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2052 GMT 4 May 94) 
  Costa Rican President-elect Jose Maria Figueres announced on 
7 May cooperation agreements with Taiwan in the financial, 
infrastructure, and agricultural areas. Taiwan will maintain 
deposit certificates for $40 million in the Central Bank of 
Costa Rica, will finance the construction of a tourist port in 
Puntarenas and a road from Naranjo to Florencia in the province 
of Alajuela, and the expansion of the ports of Limon and Mohin 
on the Atlantic coast. A Costa Rican-Taiwanese Foundation also 
will be created to facilitate credits to farmers. (Mexico City 
NOTIMEX in Spanish 2037 GMT 7 May 94) 

</TEXT>

