<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Cited on Cease-Fire With URNG </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Cited on Cease-Fire With URNG </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105024994 Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO in Spanish 10 
May 94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105024994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister General Mario Enriquez said last 
night at the headquarters of the Guatemalan Air Force: When I 
speak of a cease-fire, which hopefully will be definite in all 
areas where guerrillas are present, how joyful this would be, 
because I believe all of Guatemalan society and even 
international opinion would be satisfied, even though the URNG 
[Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity] does not have the 
resolve to carry it out. 
  Enriquez added: "I have never asked for a definitive 
cease-fire in all areas where there is a guerrilla presence. I 
have spoken exclusively of the areas between Ixcan and Xabal 
Rivers, Quiche Department, where the refugees are returning and 
where the CPR [Communities of Resistant People] are displaced. " 
  "If they (URNG) defend these people and want those who 
complain the Army has them surrounded to live in peace, they 
will, hopefully, show their political resolve with a cease-fire 
in all of the Ixcan area, because this would help the people 
join civilian life," Enriquez said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

