<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electricity Rationing Paralyzes Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electricity Rationing Paralyzes Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105040894 </F>
<F P=103> PA1105040894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial report] San Pedro Sula TIEMPO in Spanish 5 May 
94 p 2 reported that Adolfo Facusse, president of the Honduran 
Council for Private Enterprise, has announced that electricity 
rationing has paralyzed one-fourth of all national production, 
causing a daily loss of 20 million lempiras, which, if not 
halted, will cause losses amounting to 5.5 billion lempiras by 
the end of 1994. Facusse said that among the immediate solutions 
contemplated is the establishment of an electrical connection 
with Panama and Nicaragua and repairing of two thermal plants in 
Tegucigalpa and San Pedro Sula. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

