<H3> <TI>   Lewis Galindo Accepts Foreign Ministry Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lewis Galindo Accepts Foreign Ministry Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105011294 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105011294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Businessman Gabriel Lewis Galindo confirmed to RPC 
Television this afternoon that he has accepted Ernesto Perez 
Balladares' offer to hold the post of foreign minister beginning 
on 1 September. Gabriel Lewis Galindo was Panamanian ambassador 
to Washington in the last months of negotiations on the canal 
treaties and during the entire process of the ratification of 
the Torrijos-Carter Treaties. His actions were crucial to the 
ratification of the treaties. The Panamanian industrialist's 
business relations in the Americas, Europe, and Asia, as well as 
his diplomatic maneuvering ability, will be exploited by the 
Perez Balladares administration in its efforts to strengthen 
diplomatic and trade ties with all countries. 
  Lewis Galindo's acceptance of the Foreign Ministry post is 
the first confirmation of the formation of the multiparty 
cabinet promised by Dr. Perez Balladares during his presidential 
campaign. 

</TEXT>

