<F P=100> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coast Guard Intercepts Foreign Fishing Trawlers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coast Guard Intercepts Foreign Fishing Trawlers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0905231194 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1515 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0905231194 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 9 May (NA) -- A Coast Guard cutter has 
intercepted and captured two trawlers flying foreign flags. The 
trawlers were fishing illegally in the Argentine exclusive 
economic zone, without the appropriate authorization. 
  The Coast Guard cutter "Mantilla" yesterday discovered a 
foreign trawler fishing near the port of Quequen. Upon boarding 
the trawler, Coast Guard personnel confirmed the existence of 79 
metric tons of squid, hake, and codfish in the trawler's hold 
and processing line. 
  Shortly thereafter, the same Coast Guard cutter discovered 
another trawler that had already caught 146 metric tons of squid 
and rays. 
  Both trawlers were captured for violating the National 
Fishing Law, and were escorted to the port of Quequen where the 
appropriate proceedings were conducted. 

</TEXT>

