<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federal Police Strike `May Get Out of Control' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federal Police Strike `May Get Out of Control' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0905131794 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0905131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paulo Sampaio, vice president of the Brasilia 
Federal Policemen Union, fears the Federal Police strike may get 
out of control unless the government meets the policemen 
demands. The institution has been on strike for 50 days. 
  Federal policemen countrywide want salaries equal to those 
of 
the Brasilia civil police. The difference between the salaries 
of the two institutions surpasses 200 percent. 
  Federal Police Director Wilson Romao has asserted that the 
government will provide the union leaders with a proposal today. 

</TEXT>

