<F P=106> [Article by Felipe Farias] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Bahia State branch of the Brazilian Social 
Democracy Party [PSDB] has decided to support Workers Party 
presidential candidate Luis Inacio Lula da Silva. 
  The decision was made during the 8 May convention that 
officially nominated former Minister Jutahy Magalhaes, Jr., as 
the party's gubernatorial candidate for Bahia, Deputy Sergio 
Gaudenzi as vice gubernatorial candidate, and Waldir Pires as 
candidate for the Senate. 
  The position of the Bahia branch of the PSDB is deemed 
irreversible. Jutahy Magalhaes, Jr. said: "The decision has 
been made. Everywhere I go I say that my presidential candidate 
is Lula. We have already reported our decision to the party and 
to Fernando Henrique Cardoso." [passage omitted] 

